args: Ahhh, what a good day...\nI ate so many different things.
I can't wait to see what exciting new food\nI'll get to try tomorrow!
Huh? Who's arguing this late at night?
I'm telling you, I know EXACTLY\nwhat matters most to royalty!
Huh? Oh, hey, Pecorine. Yeah, so I was\njust having a fight with ol' Nefaria here.
We merely seek concord as to how royalty\nought behave and what qualities they\nmust possess.
I hold that nobility of spirit must be at the\nfore—and that a regent must treasure the\ngladness of one's people above all.
A country cannot exist with rulers alone;\nit claims its title only because of the\nsmallfolk who see fit to dwell within.

When a ruler grants boons to a people,
they respond with kindness in kind;
ofttimes even enough to raise the very
dead themselves.
I know this well, for it is my own tale.
Yar, I ain't denying that people's\nhappiness is important.
But what you need to keep folks happy\nisn't will—it's STRENGTH!

The strength to stay free and not bend to
the whims of others! Any country that
lacks strength is gonna be wearing a yoke
around their neck until the end of time.
If a country lacks power, they'll lose\neverything: Their goods, their pride...\nand eventually, their lives.
I don't regret choosing to live as a pirate,\nbut if I'd been born a princess with power,\nmy life would have been very different.
Hmm, yes. I think I see where you're\nboth coming from.
And I have a perfect solution: food!
You're only fighting because you're hangry,\nso I'm gonna fill you both to the brim\nwith food AND happiness!
Now let's head for the kitchen so I can\nwhip you two kids up some supper.
How does this scapegrace possess\nsuch feverish strength?!
Some nice, hot chazuke—the perfect\nlate-night snack.
T'would be the height of discourtesy to\nturn down the aliments of another, so...
Marry, but this is a wonder!\nSo light, yet so flavorful!
I feel like I could eat a mountain of this\nstuff. You got any more hanging around?
Certainly! Eat as much as you like.
It's good to see you two smiling again.\nThat's the power of food!
There's lots of things that make people\nhappy, but I think food is number one.
Because whether you're rich or poor,\ngood food makes everyone smile.
And a country where everyone can enjoy\ngood chow and good times is my ideal!
Indeed, it is most befitting of you.
But filling the bellies of an entire country\nisn't as easy as it sounds.
If you want to make it happen, you need\nboth of the things you two were arguing\nabout earlier.
You need a noble spirit that cares for your\npeople AND the strength to protect them.
Heh. When you put it that way,\nit actually makes a ton of sense.
Sorry for getting my pantaloons in a twist\nabout something so dumb, Nefaria.
Hearing people talk about royalty just\nreminds me of my old life, I guess.
Nay, the fault is mine; I permitted my\nemotions in the matter to run amok.
'Tis a subject strongly associated with the\nmemories I have lost, and I oft find myself\novercome by the power of it.
Pray forgive my rudeness;\nI would ever stand your friend.
Glad everything's better. Now bring it in!
I'm so sorry! I was just so happy you\nmade up that I couldn't help myself.
*sigh* You really are one of a kind.
One minute it's like you're not thinking\nanything at all, and the next you're deeper\nthan the briny blue itself!
When you spoke previous of your ideals,\nit was clear they come from the workings\nof your daily life.
Were you perhaps a woman of noble\nstanding in your original world?
I...don't know what you're talking about!\nNot a clue! Ah ha ha ha...haaaa?
Yep! I'm just the perpetually peckish\nPecorine—an ordinary girl found hungry\non the ground!
